---
title: "Making the most of the ‘crisortunity’: Techno-fixes and precarity in a global pandemic"
collection: publications
permalink: /publication/2022-12-02-crisortunity
excerpt: 'What does a robust and useful technological response to a crisis, aware and attentive to the biases and messages of digital media, look like?'
date: 2022-12-02
venue: 'Interdisciplinary Digital Engagement in Arts & Humanities (IDEAH)'
paperurl: 'https://ideah.pubpub.org/pub/vpuit7w4/release/2'
citation: 'Bryant, Haley, Nelanthi Hewa, Camille Inston and Arun Jacob (2022).“Making the most of the ‘crisortunity’: Techno-fixes and precarity in a global pandemic” Interdisciplinary Digital Engagement in Arts & Humanities (IDEAH), vol. 3, no. 2, Dec 02, 2022. https://doi.org/10.21428/f1f23564.db5a6abe.'
---
 This paper thus explores the implications of qualifying something as a “crisis” with a discrete beginning and end, and what it might mean to offer fixes to something that is broken rather than curating, managing, repairing, or caring for something that is not yet irreparable. 

[Download paper here](https://ideah.pubpub.org/pub/vpuit7w4/release/2)

Recommended citation: Bryant, Haley, Nelanthi Hewa, Camille Inston and Arun Jacob (2022).“Making the most of the ‘crisortunity’: Techno-fixes and precarity in a global pandemic” Interdisciplinary Digital Engagement in Arts & Humanities (IDEAH), vol. 3, no. 2, Dec 02, 2022. https://doi.org/10.21428/f1f23564.db5a6abe.
